contain shell commands by design and so are generally considered
trusted.

I remember using this trick in an exploit once :)

$ printf "exploit, iprog=/usr/bin/id,\n" | tic -
$ TERM=exploit reset
uid=1000(taviso) gid=1000(taviso)

